quran[17]{c,v,t}:
  19,66,"Yet the human being continues to ask, \"When I am dead, will I then be brought out alive again"
  19,67,"Does the human being not remember that We created him before, when he was nothing"
  19,68,"So by your Lord, We will surely round them up along with the devils, and then We will bring them around Hell on their knees"
  19,69,"Then from every sect, We will drag out those who were the most defiant towards the Merciful"
  19,70,"Surely, We know best who most deserves the fire of Hell"
  19,71,And all of you will go through it. This is a decree from your Lord that must be fulfilled
  19,72,Then We will save those who were mindful of God and leave the unjust on their knees
  19,73,"And when Our verses, which are perfectly clear, are recited to them, the unbelievers say to those who believe, \"Which of [our] two parties is in the better position and enjoys superior influence"
  19,74,"And yet how many generations have We destroyed before them who surpassed them in possessions and [outward] appearance"
  19,75,"Say, \"As for him who is lost, let the Merciful-to-all lengthen the span of his days until they see what they were promised, punishment either [in this world] or at the Hour [of Judgment]. Then they will clearly see who is worse in possessions and who has the weaker forces"
  19,76,"To those rightly guided, God increases guidance, and the good deeds that will last are those that are deemed best and most rewarding in your Lord's sight"
  19,77,"Have you considered the man who denies the truth of Our signs and says, \"I will surely be given wealth and children"
  19,78,"Has he received extrasensory knowledge, or has he received a pledge from the Merciful"
  19,79,No! We will record what he says and extend the duration of his punishment
  19,80,"And We will inherit from him the things he's talks about, and he will come to Us alone"
  19,81,"And they have taken gods other than God, hoping that they would be [a source of] strength for them"
  19,82,No! Those deities will reject their worship and will even turn against them